   PRIESTS-SCHOOL _ They are men in black lined up row by row,
table by table, in the refractory of the North American College,
the Vatican's school for American priests. They will spend up to
five years here. And, at the end of their studies, those among the
seminarians who keep the faith will leave this place, officially
set apart by God and the Catholic church for a life of devotion and
celibacy. (White, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
