this A's sale all wrong. Maybe Major League Baseball is happy with
Andy Dolich and George Zimmer and Bob Piccinini and the depth and
breadth of their portfolios. Maybe Bud Selig and the owners for
whom he serves don't care who owns the A's as long as someone does,
and as long as they stay in Oakland. By RAY RATTO.
