<P>
   WONG-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ Whenever our society experiences
something like the Littleton, Colo., school massacre, politicians
feel they must ``do something'' in response. So President Clinton
and Congress have been mucking about in a bunch of ideas they hope
will stop such a tragedy in the future. By WILLIAM WONG.
</P>
<P>
   OCEAN-LIVING (San Francisco) _ One reason I live in San
Francisco (actually, Mill Valley) is because the city is situated
right next to the wildest wilderness there is: the sea. I believe
it is important to occasionally encounter the wilderness of the
sea. A taste of salt spray is an elixir that refreshes your
awareness and adds zip to your outlook on life. By HUEY D. JOHNSON.
