<P>
   Phil Currie's vision of tyrannosaurus is horrifying: packs of
monsters that stayed together and slayed together. Currie believes
that on top of a ridge in the desolate Canadian wilderness he'll
find a treasure trove of dinosaur bones. And those old fossils
could bolster his theory that two-footed carnivores traveled in
groups, with fleet youngsters driving prey into the powerful jaws
of waiting adults.
