that prosperity was just around the corner. But former employees
and other industry experts think optimism is premature. Penney's
stock may be undervalued because of the strong performance of the
Eckerd's drugstore chain, they say. But the core of the business _
the nearly century-old retail chain _ is as troubled as ever. By
Leslie Kaufman.
