majority of the poorest Americans, particularly children, are
covered by Medicaid for dental care, they are not getting it. Most
dentists tend to be loath to take Medicaid patients and Medicaid
patients, often with transportation and daycare problems, are
likelier to miss appointments. By Carey Goldberg. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NY-SCHOOLS (New York) _ When New York City Schools Chancellor
Rudy Crew announced a sweeping shake-up earlier in the week,
closing 13 low performing schools and taking direct control of 43
others, Robert E. Riccobono, the superintendent known for some
innovative programs in District 9, was among those fired. His fate
is a telling example of the difficulty in reforming the city's
worst school district. By James Yardley.  &QL;
