Angeles. ``And I think he has already done that to some degree.''
</P>
<P>
   The Spanish-speaking Bush's more moderate message could attract
some Hispanics to the Republican fold.
</P>
<P>
   ``It may be some very fertile ground for him to plow,'' Pachon
said of the Hispanic voter in California.
</P>
<P>
   Bush also may run into trouble in California on two other thorny
issues: guns and abortion.
</P>
<P>
   Bruce Cain, a political science professor at the University of
