baby switching incident at the University of Virginia hospital.
Precision Dynamics Inc. is being sued by Paula Johnson, the mother
of one of the babies who claims that the identification bands'
defective design allowed them to fall off her daughter and another
child, leading to the inadvertent switch. The suit was filed
Wednesday in Los Angeles Superior Court. By Enrique Rivero. (Will
move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
