invading French troops used the full-size clay model for crossbow
practice. Leonardo never completed the piece, which would have been
the largest equestrian sculpture in the world. Today, Leonardo's
dream, first articulated as a postage-stamp-size sketch, was
revealed in three jaw-dropping dimensions, in the form of a proudly
prancing 15-ton bronze stallion that was cast and assembled at a
foundry here, 60 miles north of New York City.
