<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Holiday Inn finds room for suites
 &HT;    By Shelia M. Poole
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Your next family vacation or business trip to Orlando,
Fla., may have just gotten a bit user-friendly.
</P>
<P>
   On July 1, the first all-suite Holiday Inn Resort will open in
Orlando with 800 suites catering to travelers with a variety of
interests, from movie-lovers to fitness buffs and couples wanting a
quiet romantic weekend.
</P>
<P>
   The $80 million property, Holiday Inn Family Suites Resort Lake
Buena Vista, will be located near Epcot Center.
</P>
<P>
   ``The concept is a sequel to kids' suites, which has been so
widely accepted by customers,'' said Terry Whaples, operating
partner for the project.
</P>
<P>
   Suburban Atlanta-based Bass Hotels &AMP; Resorts' other brands
include Crowne Plaza, Inter-Continental, Holiday Inns, Holiday Inn
Select, Holiday Inn Express and Staybridge Suites.
</P>
<P>
   Whaples said other sites are under consideration, though she
declined to identify them.
</P>
<P>
   While theme hotels are not new in the industry, it's unusual to
find so many different themes in one property, experts say.
</P>
<P>
   The hotel's main drawing card is its 487 Kidsuites, targeted at
families with kids. The two-bedroom suites will have a separate
parlor area with 25-inch television, pull-out sofa and game table.
The suite also will include an adult bedroom and fun-theme kid's
room with bunk beds, video cassette player and Nintendo 64.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it's been proven that there's a market,'' said Paul
Puryear, a lodging analyst with Raymond James in Tampa, Fla. ``And
this one is in Orlando, which is destination number one for family
travel.''
</P>
<P>
   But kids aren't the only ones being targeted in Orlando. Here's
a sampling of other suites.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cinemasuites: These dozen suites could be called couch potato
heaven. Each features a king bedroom and separate theater room with
a 60-inch color television, surround-sound stereo system and dual
recliners with footrests. The suite also includes a ``reel
package'' of two video rentals, a bag of microwave popcorn and
soda.
</P>
<P>
   _ Fitness Suites: A good deal for those who want to pig out on
vacation, but don't want to feel too guilty about it. Each suite
features a recumbent bike, free weights, exercise mat and abdominal
bench.
</P>
<P>
   Others include a business suite with four-seat conference area
and separate modem line and a residential suite featuring a 50-inch
television and full-service kitchen.
</P>
<P>
   Room rates range from $130 to $160.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
