<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the additional
story for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Saturday, June 26, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Veronica Villarreal at (206) 448-8342.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-DILLON (FEDERAL WAY, Wash.) _ There are baby pictures on the
wall, the table and the big-screen television set. A padded baby
carrier sits next to the leather couch. This is home for Corey
Dillon, one of the most talented, and perhaps misunderstood,
athletes to emerge from Seattle. His name is in the NFL and
University of Washington record books, his jersey in pro football's
hall of fame, rewards for carrying a football like no other. Yet
you should see Dillon, 24, run a juice bottle to his daughter,
6-month-old Cameron Antoine-Dillon.
</P>
<P>
   By Dan Raley. (Story has moved in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
</TEXT>
