 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-FANFAIR-NASHVILLE-NYT (moved on Sunday, June 20)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, June 20,
about the country music Fan Fair at the Tennessee State Fairgrounds
in Nashville and an accompanying picture caption misspelled the
surname of a star who did not attend. She is Reba McEntire, not
McIntyre.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-FADIMAN-NYT (moved on Sunday, June 20)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Clifton Fadiman sent by the New York Times News
Service on Sunday, June 20, misspelled the surname of a critic of
Mr. Fadiman's role as a popularizer of intellectual subjects. He
was Dwight Macdonald, not MacDonald.
</P>
<P>
   BC-BOOK-TALK-NYT (moved on Wednesday, June 23)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, June
23, about a new edition of William Strunk Jr. and E.B. White's
``Elements of Style,'' misspelled the surname of the author of
``Simple and Direct: A Rhetoric for Writers.'' He is Jacques
Barzun, not Barzan.
</P>
