-- Craig Arnoff, 8, looks at ``Il Cavallo'' a 24-foot-tall bronze
sculpture of a horse which is faithful to a design by Leonardo da
Vinci on Friday some 60 miles north of New York City. The public
showing here is the last step before the sculpture's seven pieces
are dismantled and flown in an Alitalia jumbo jet to Milan, where
the horse will be erected on a pedestal, welded into a single
piece, and unveiled on September 10, the 500th anniversary of the
day the French army occupied the Ducal palace and disfigured Da
Vinci's original prototype. (Joyce Dopkeen/New York Times Photo)
