<SLUG> BC-SLEEPWALKING-MURDER-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`SLEEPWALKING' DEFENSE FAILS TO SAVE KILLER  
(DW)
</HEADLINE>
   c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX _ A Phoenix man who said he stabbed his wife 44 times
and drowned her while he was sleepwalking was convicted of
first-degree murder Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors have said they will seek the death penalty against
the man, Scott Falater, 43, in the Jan. 16, 1997, death of his
wife, Yarmila, the mother of their two children. A hearing is
scheduled for Aug. 20.
</P>
<P>
   The Maricopa County Superior Court jury here deliberated for
eight hours.
</P>
<P>
   It was undisputed that Falater stabbed his wife 44 times with a
hunting knife outside their home, dragged her to the family
swimming pool, held her head under water and then changed his
clothes. He put the clothes and the murder weapon inside a plastic
container in his car.
</P>
<P>
   Falater said he was fast asleep during the episode and
remembered nothing from that night.  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
